  "prompt": "Is there something that Sachin Tendulkar has not done in cricket?",
  "response": "Sachin Tendulkar, often regarded as one of the greatest cricketers of all time, has achieved numerous records and milestones in his illustrious career. However, there are a few notable things he has not done in cricket:\n\n1. **Win an ICC World T20**: Tendulkar was part of the Indian team that won the 2011 ICC Cricket World Cup, but he retired before India's victory in the 2013 ICC World T20.\n\n2. **Score a Triple Century in Test Cricket**: While Tendulkar scored 100 centuries across Test and ODI cricket, he never managed to score a triple century in Test matches, a feat achieved by players like Virender Sehwag and Chris Gayle.\n\n3. **Captain India to a Test Series Win in South Africa**: Tendulkar captained India in several matches, but he was never able to lead the team to a Test series victory in South Africa.\n\n4. **Play in the Indian Premier League (IPL)**: Tendulkar did play in the IPL, representing Mumbai Indians, but he retired before the league fully matured into the competitive and globally recognized tournament it is today.\n\n5. **Score a Century in All Countries He Played In**: Tendulkar scored centuries in many countries, but he never scored a century in Bangladesh or Zimbabwe.\n\nThese are some of the few things that Sachin Tendulkar has not accomplished in his cricketing career, despite his extraordinary achievements and contributions to the sport.",
